            ("Can the Scrum Master also be a Developer on the same team?", "Scrum Master可以同時擔任同一團隊的開發人員嗎？", ["Yes, but it is not recommended as it may compromise effectiveness", "No, this is strictly forbidden", "Yes, this is the recommended approach", "Only for small teams"], ["可以，但不推薦，因為可能影響有效性", "不可以，這是嚴格禁止的", "可以，這是推薦的方法", "僅適用於小型團隊"], 0, "The Scrum Guide doesn't forbid it, but notes the focus on two very different accountabilities may reduce effectiveness in both areas. It's not recommended.", "Scrum指南不禁止，但指出專注於兩個非常不同的責任可能降低兩個領域的有效性。不推薦。"),
            ("Stakeholders in Scrum are:", "Scrum中的利害關係人是：", ["Anyone with a stake in the product who provides input but is not on the Scrum Team", "Only the Product Owner", "Only company executives", "Only end users"], ["對產品有利益關係、提供意見但不在Scrum團隊中的任何人", "僅產品負責人", "僅公司高管", "僅最終用戶"], 0, "Stakeholders include users, customers, sponsors, management, and anyone affected by or interested in the product. They interact primarily through Sprint Review.", "利害關係人包括用戶、客戶、贊助人、管理層以及受產品影響或對產品有興趣的任何人。主要通過Sprint Review互動。"),
