            ("The Product Backlog is:", "產品待辦列表是：", ["An ordered list of everything known to be needed in the product, the single source of requirements", "A fixed plan that cannot change", "Only a list of bugs", "A Gantt chart"], ["已知產品所需一切內容的有序列表，是需求的唯一來源", "不能更改的固定計劃", "僅錯誤列表", "甘特圖"], 0, "The Product Backlog is dynamic, constantly evolving to identify what the product needs. It's the single source of work for the Scrum Team.", "產品待辦列表是動態的，不斷演變以識別產品需求。它是Scrum團隊工作的唯一來源。"),
            ("The Sprint Backlog consists of:", "Sprint Backlog由以下組成：", ["The Sprint Goal, selected Product Backlog items, and an actionable plan for delivering the Increment", "All items in the Product Backlog", "Only the Sprint Goal", "A list of completed work"], ["Sprint目標、選定的產品待辦列表項目以及交付增量的可行動計劃", "產品待辦列表中的所有項目", "僅Sprint目標", "已完成工作的列表"], 0, "Sprint Backlog = Sprint Goal + selected PBIs + plan to deliver them as Increment. It's a real-time picture of the work Developers plan to accomplish.", "Sprint Backlog = Sprint目標 + 選定的PBI + 將其作為增量交付的計劃。它是開發人員計劃完成工作的實時圖片。"),
            ("The Increment is:", "增量是：", ["The sum of all Product Backlog items completed during a Sprint and all prior Sprints, meeting the Definition of Done", "Only the items completed in the current Sprint", "A prototype", "A draft version"], ["在當前Sprint和所有先前Sprint中完成的所有產品待辦列表項目的總和，符合完成的定義", "僅在當前Sprint中完成的項目", "原型", "草稿版本"], 0, "An Increment is a concrete stepping stone toward the Product Goal. Each Increment is additive and must work together. Multiple Increments can be created within a Sprint.", "增量是邁向產品目標的具體墊腳石。每個增量是累加的，必須協同工作。一個Sprint內可以創建多個增量。"),
            ("Each artifact in Scrum has a corresponding commitment. The commitment for the Product Backlog is:", "Scrum中的每個工件都有對應的承諾。產品待辦列表的承諾是：", ["The Product Goal", "The Sprint Goal", "The Definition of Done", "The Increment"], ["產品目標", "Sprint目標", "完成的定義", "增量"], 0, "Product Goal → Product Backlog commitment; Sprint Goal → Sprint Backlog commitment; Definition of Done → Increment commitment.", "產品目標 → 產品待辦列表承諾；Sprint目標 → Sprint Backlog承諾；完成的定義 → 增量承諾。"),
            ("The Definition of Done (DoD) is:", "完成的定義（DoD）是：", ["A formal description of the state of the Increment when it meets the quality measures required for the product", "A to-do list for Developers", "The Sprint Goal", "Only a test plan"], ["增量狀態的正式描述，當增量滿足產品所需的質量標準時", "開發人員的待辦事項列表", "Sprint目標", "僅測試計劃"], 0, "DoD is a quality standard. When a PBI meets the DoD, an Increment is born. It creates transparency about what state each item must be in to be considered complete.", "DoD是質量標準。當PBI符合DoD時，增量就誕生了。它為每個項目必須處於何種狀態才能被視為完成創造了透明度。"),
            ("Multiple Scrum Teams working on the same product should:", "多個Scrum團隊在同一產品上工作時應：", ["Share the same Product Goal and Definition of Done, but have separate Sprint Backlogs", "Have separate Product Backlogs", "Never communicate with each other", "Have one Sprint Backlog for all teams"], ["共享相同的產品目標和完成的定義，但有各自的Sprint Backlog", "有各自的產品待辦列表", "永遠不互相溝通", "所有團隊共用一個Sprint Backlog"], 0, "Multiple teams on one product share the same Product Backlog, Product Goal, and Definition of Done. Each team has its own Sprint Backlog.", "多個團隊在同一產品上工作時共享相同的產品待辦列表、產品目標和完成的定義。每個團隊有自己的Sprint Backlog。"),
            ("Product Backlog refinement is:", "產品待辦列表梳理是：", ["The act of breaking down and further defining items into smaller, more precise items", "Only re-ordering items", "A formal Scrum event", "Removing items from the backlog"], ["將項目分解並進一步定義為更小、更精確項目的行為", "僅重新排列項目", "正式的Scrum事件", "從待辦列表中移除項目"], 0, "Refinement involves adding details, estimates, and order to items. The Scrum Team decides how, when, and how much refinement is needed. It typically consumes ~10% of capacity.", "梳理涉及為項目添加詳細信息、估算和優先順序。Scrum團隊決定如何、何時以及需要多少梳理。通常消耗約10%的產能。"),
            ("If the Developers determine they have too much or too little work during the Sprint, they should:", "如果開發人員在Sprint期間確定工作量過多或過少，應：", ["Negotiate scope with the Product Owner without affecting the Sprint Goal", "Cancel the Sprint", "Add more work from the Product Backlog without consulting anyone", "Extend the Sprint duration"], ["與產品負責人協商範圍，不影響Sprint目標", "取消Sprint", "不經任何人同意從產品待辦列表添加更多工作", "延長Sprint持續時間"], 0, "Developers can negotiate scope with the PO as they learn more. The Sprint Goal cannot be compromised. If scope is removed, it goes back to the Product Backlog.", "開發人員可以在了解更多情況後與PO協商範圍。Sprint目標不能妥協。如果範圍被移除，它回到產品待辦列表。"),
            ("The Product Goal is:", "產品目標是：", ["The long-term objective for the Scrum Team, providing a target for planning", "The same as the Sprint Goal", "Set by the Scrum Master", "Only about revenue targets"], ["Scrum團隊的長期目標，為規劃提供目標", "與Sprint目標相同", "由Scrum Master設定", "僅關於收入目標"], 0, "Product Goal describes the future state of the product and serves as a target for the Scrum Team to plan against. Only one Product Goal at a time.", "產品目標描述產品的未來狀態，作為Scrum團隊規劃的目標。一次只有一個產品目標。"),
            ("An Increment cannot be released until:", "增量在以下情況之前不能發布：", ["There is no rule preventing release at any time during the Sprint—it can be released whenever it is Done", "The Sprint ends", "The PO approves the release", "The stakeholders approve"], ["沒有規則阻止在Sprint期間任何時間發布——完成即可發布", "Sprint結束", "PO批准發布", "利害關係人批准"], 0, "The Scrum Guide places no prescribed release timing. An Increment can be released at any point during the Sprint. The decision is a product decision, not a Scrum rule.", "Scrum指南沒有規定發布時間。增量可以在Sprint期間的任何時間發布。決定是產品決策，而非Scrum規則。"),
